<span id="v.iv.ix.xviii"></span>

<span id="v.iv.ix.xviii-p1"></span> <span class="c11"><span
id="v.iv.ix.xviii-p1.1"></span>Chapter 18.—</span>34.  Irenæus of
Ululi <span id="fr_1810"></span>[1811](#fn_1810.md) said:  "If the Church
does not baptize a heretic, because it is said that he has been baptized
already, then heresy is the greater." <span
id="fr_1811"></span>[1812](#fn_1811.md)

<span id="v.iv.ix.xviii-p4"></span>35.  The answer is:  On the same
principle it might be said, If therefore the Church does not baptize the
covetous man, because it is said that he has been baptized already, then
covetousness is the greater.  But this is false, therefore the other is
also false.

